        "text": "Conclusion and rationale\n- In aqueous solution, CuBr+ is more stable than CuCl+ (i.e., β1 is larger for bromide than for chloride) at comparable temperature/ionic strength. This aligns with the general trend that the borderline-soft Cu(II) binds the more polarizable halides more strongly (Br− > Cl−).",
